Comparable is used for the natural ordering of objects and is implemented inside the class using the compareTo() method.

Comparator is used for custom sorting and is implemented in a separate class or as a lambda using the compare() method.

We use Comparable when there is only one default sorting order (for example, sorting employees by ID). We use Comparator when we need multiple sorting options, such as by salary, name, or age.

Easy Remember

Comparable → Inside the class → compareTo()
Comparator → Outside the class → compare()
