Difference between ArrayList, Vector and CopyOnWriteArrayList.
Ideal Answer

ArrayList

Not thread-safe
Fast for read operations
Capacity grows by approximately 50% when full.

Vector

Thread-safe because methods are synchronized
Legacy collection
Capacity doubles (100%) by default when full.

CopyOnWriteArrayList

Thread-safe
On every write operation (add, remove, update), it creates a new copy of the underlying array.
Best when reads are much more frequent than writes.
Its iterator does not throw ConcurrentModificationException.
Question 2
Checked vs Unchecked Exception
Ideal Answer

Checked Exceptions

Checked at compile time.
Must be handled or declared using throws.
Examples:
IOException
SQLException
FileNotFoundException

Unchecked Exceptions

Occur at runtime.
Extend RuntimeException.
Examples:
NullPointerException
ArithmeticException
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

We avoid catching generic Exception because it hides the real cause and makes debugging harder.

Correction: ClassNotFoundException is a checked exception, but in interviews, IOException and SQLException are more common examples.

