Index

An index is a data structure that improves the speed of data retrieval by reducing the number of rows the database must scan.

Can indexes hurt performance?

Yes.

Because every INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE must also update the index. Too many indexes slow down write operations and consume
additional storage.

